dreams.dream:
In my dream I had a loose upper molar, it was the left one.  I was in a lot of pain but didn't know what to do about it. I remember someone was kissing me, I think it was a woman who I really care about. She wanted to make out and I wanted to respond and not having to explain anything about my loose tooth. I had trouble opening my mouth but didn't want to stop the kissing nor did I want her to notice.

I also remember that my ex was in the dream. In real life he and I separated violently, almost a year ago, and we are in the process of divorce.

In the dream I think he was trying to give me comfort. And I think I accepted that and also thought it was nice.
dreams.interpretation:
The loose upper molar in your dream may symbolize a sense of instability or insecurity in your life. It could indicate that something important or foundational to you is becoming uncertain or shaky, causing you pain and unease.

The presence of the woman you care about and the desire to respond positively to her suggests a longing for emotional connection and intimacy. You may want to have a close, romantic relationship where you can be vulnerable and open with another person. However, the difficulty in opening your mouth and not wanting her to notice the loose tooth suggests that you may be hesitant or reluctant to reveal your vulnerabilities and imperfections to her. You want to present yourself as strong and unaffected, rather than burdening her with your issues.

The appearance of your ex in the dream, particularly in a comforting role, may indicate that you are still processing and seeking closure or healing from the past relationship. Despite the separation being violent, your subconscious may be acknowledging that you still find some level of comfort or solace in his presence. This could be a sign that you are in the process of reconciling or coming to terms with the ending of that relationship.

Overall, the dream suggests a desire for connection and emotional support, while also highlighting your inner struggle to balance vulnerability and the fear of being judged or rejected. It may be beneficial for you to explore these emotions and vulnerabilities further in order to find healing and fulfillment in your relationships.
dreams.title: Fragile Kisses: A Dream of Pain, Longing, and Unexpected Comfort

This dream could symbolize concerns about your physical appearance or self-image. The act of hitting your tooth suggests an unexpected or unintentional change or damage to your self-perception. The fear of your tooth being broken reflects your fear of losing or damaging something that is important to you.

The fact that in the dream your left tooth is the one that is broken, even though you hit your right tooth, indicates that there may be an imbalance between your fears and reality. It suggests that your worries or anxieties may not align with the actual risks or concerns in your waking life.

Overall, this dream may be a reflection of your fears of external judgment, loss of attractiveness, or perceived flaws. It could be beneficial to examine your own self-image and confidence, and explore any underlying concerns that may be contributing to these insecurities.

dreams.dream: soñe que me daba comezon la nariz y me salia una mosca, cuando respiraba me volvia a querer entrar mas moscas, hasta el punto que eran muchas que no me dejaban respirar y me tapaba tratando de que no siguieran entrando a mi nariz, hasta que utilizaba un insecticida echándomelo dentro de la nariz para matar las moscas

Cada vez que respiras y aparecen más moscas, sugiere que los problemas o desafíos a los que te enfrentas se están volviendo abrumadores y dificultan tu capacidad de encontrar comodidad o paz.

Cubrir tu nariz en un intento de evitar que las moscas entren significa tu deseo de protegerte y encontrar alivio de estas frustraciones. Sin embargo, a pesar de tus mejores esfuerzos, las moscas continúan persistiendo, lo que indica que los desafíos a los que te enfrentas pueden parecer incontrolables o imparables.

El acto de usar insecticida y verterlo en tu nariz para matar a las moscas podría representar tu necesidad de tomar medidas drásticas o encontrar una solución para eliminar estas dificultades de tu vida. Sugiere que estás dispuesto/a a enfrentar y erradicar estas molestias u obstáculos, incluso si esto implica recurrir a medidas extremas.

En general, este sueño puede reflejar tu conciencia subconsciente de las irritaciones y desafíos en tu vida despierta que se han vuelto abrumadores o difíciles de manejar. Podría ser una representación simbólica de tu deseo de eliminar estas influencias negativas y recuperar un sentido de control y paz.

dreams.dream:
I dreamt that I was at work, the chairs are there were changes of places, they put a friend's partner right in my place, we both work together, I felt uncomfortable as if I had invaded my space, I had worked with that person before, but I felt guilty once because I accidentally deleted her work one day and she got mad at me but later she forgot about it, then the work area became like a classroom, people passed in front, I was in the back chatting with my friend, then I passed by and I remember there were candies and chocolates, like candy and chocolates, as if they were in a classroom.
then the work area became like a classroom, people were passing in front, I was at the back talking with my friend, then I passed and I remember there were candies and chocolates, like little m&m, we were talking about work experiences and possible changes of people in the teams, the table where the chocolates were was yellow, I could taste the m&m in the dream as if they were real.
later i was in another scene, this one was more lugubrious, i was in the streets of the center of my city, there was a dark march, i think it was of satan, they were carrying a skeleton like a ram with golden horns, adorned with black cloth, all the people were like gothic and they were walking in shadowy silence, looking towards the ground, I think they were even carrying an incense burner, I felt a little uncomfortable, like when I look at bats since those animals in real life give me irrational fear because of their gothic wings, in a corner my family and I stopped to see a sign where the route of the march was mentioned, it specified a neogothic style temple that exists in my city, it is the size and style of the french gothic cathedrals, I began to protest my anger for that march, it also sounded like contempt towards the gothic, I said why would they go through that temple if it is catholic, besides the stone of the neogothic temple is white, the opposite of the black of the gothic, in thoseenti as a gothic woman gave me forcibly three turns in the direction of the hands of the clock while she seemed to recite some things in a low voice, as if it were a curse, that woman I do not know, she was pale and with black hair up, also dressed in black, what I did in the dream was to give three turns in the opposite direction and saying I cancel this curse.

To give context my friend is very sweet, she is very catholic, many tell me that she should be my girlfriend but I don't like her that way, even so she is a very close friend.
I work in gps, in fact yesterday I was adding information about gay pride marches.
Yesterday night I went to water the plants in my backyard, I was afraid because at that time bats fly and I was afraid to see them, the black of their wings and their shape scare me.
dreams.interpretation:
This dream seems to contain various symbols and emotions, which may reflect different aspects of your life and subconscious mind. Here is a possible interpretation for the different elements in your dream:

1. Changing chairs at work: This could represent feelings of displacement or discomfort in your work environment. It may suggest that you feel like your position or role is being invaded or altered.

2. Accidentally deleting your friend's work: This might indicate a sense of guilt or worry about making mistakes or causing harm in your relationships. It could reflect your fear of disappointing or angering someone close to you.

3. Work area transforming into a classroom: This shift could symbolize a desire for learning, growth, or a change in your career. It may also suggest that you are discussing and reflecting on past experiences or considering different approaches to your work.

4. Candy and chocolates: These sweet treats could represent rewards or positive experiences related to your work. They might symbolize the enjoyment and satisfaction you derive from your professional achievements.

5. Dark march in the city: The dark and gothic atmosphere, along with the presence of the Satan figure, may indicate feelings of unease, fear, or inner conflict. It could represent hidden or suppressed aspects of yourself that you find disturbing or unsettling.

6. Neogothic temple: This symbolizes your cultural or religious background. Your anger towards the march going through the temple might suggest a clash between your personal beliefs and external influences. It may reflect a struggle with reconciling different aspects of your identity or experiencing frustration when your values are challenged.

7. Gothic woman cursing you: This mysterious woman could represent the shadow side of yourself or an external influence that is imposing negative thoughts or energies upon you. Your action of canceling the curse demonstrates your determination to resist and overcome these negative effects.

Overall, this dream may reflect your concerns about work dynamics, feelings of guilt or fear of making mistakes, desires for personal or professional growth, and struggles with reconciling different aspects of your identity and values. It is essential to reflect on these symbols and emotions in the context of your own life experiences and feelings to gain a deeper understanding of their meaning for you.
dreams.title: Workplace Invasion and Gothic Procession: A Surreal Dream Journey

dreams.dream: Soñé que un amigo y yo, estabamos al parecer volando o levitando, recuerdo que una voz que no conozco o un ser nos advirtió sobre no ir a cierto lugar porque era muy peligroso, sin embargo, mi amigo vio a una persona que él conocía en el lugar al que no debíamos ir, y fue así allí. Yo había caído en un lugar oscuro donde había una iluminación muy tenue con subtonos azules, estaba lleno de literas enormes por todos lados, en ellas había colchones blancos, no estaban limpios, pero tampoco sucios, no lograba decifrar cuantos colchones a lo largo eran y mucho menos a los anchos, tampoco lograba ver el final de la habitación, todo estaba muy oscuro, cuando a lo lejos, logro ver un letrero neon con las letras EXIT a lo lejos, decido ir hacia él, pero mientras me muevo por los colchones, veo huesos sobre ellos, conforme avanzaba la cantidad de huesos regados aumentaba, y entonces, sentí que había alguien o algo más moviendose sobre los colchones, el rechinar de los resortes de los colchones me hizo dar cuenta de que esa cosa era grande, cuando sintió que yo estaba presente comenzó a buscarme, primero de manera normal, pero al darse cuenta de que sí había alguien con él, aumentó su velocidad y sus ansias de encontrarme. Me di cuenta de que era una criatura humanoide, delgada y huesuda, de piel tan palida que lucía ligeramente azul por la iluminación, cabello largo y destrozado, tenía cadenas colgando pero era libre de moverse, estaban rotas. Cuando se desesperó porque yo huía de aquello, comenzó a romper los colchones para llegar a mí, yo nunca pude hacer más que tratar de huir, y nunca sentí que avanzaba hacia la salida, entre más me acercaba más lejos se veía. Esa cosa estaba tan cerca de mí y el miedo que sentía era espantoso y abrumador, cuando estaba a punto de tocarme, desperté.

Sin embargo, puede verse tentado a ignorar las advertencias e ir por ese camino de todos modos. El lugar oscuro en el que cayó puede representar un espacio negativo o una situación peligrosa en la que se encuentra. Las literas con huesos en ellas pueden representar una pérdida de vida o una pérdida de algún aspecto de su vida. La criatura que lo persigue podría representar su miedo a lo desconocido o el miedo a confrontar una situación. Las emociones que siente en el sueño sugieren que está abrumado y se siente atrapado, y que siente que no hay escape de la situación en la que se encuentra. Puede ser una advertencia para escuchar su intuición y evitar cualquier cosa que no sea segura para usted.
